    <section class="brutus-text-section">
        <h2 class="brutus-text-title">About Brutus</h2>
        <p>
            Brutus is a game developed to experience tactics and excitement in not getting caught, the game is a stealth game that challenges you to navigate a dangerous environment without being seen, blending strategy, timing, and cunning. You must read your surroundings, anticipate enemy movements, and strike only when the moment is right. Success doesn’t come from brute force, but from patience, precision, and the art of staying hidden. Whether you’re infiltrating high-security compounds, eavesdropping on critical conversations, or escaping undetected, every decision matters... and one wrong move could mean failure.
        </p>
    </section>
    
    <section class="brutus-text-section">
        <h2 class="brutus-text-title">About The Developers</h2>
        <p>
            The game is developed by two friends who share the same ideals when it comes to software development. My name is Simon dos Reis Spedsbjerg and with Rasmus Meldgaard we decided to develop this project. We both share the same ideals in software design, with a focus on proper design, software architecture and methodologies which makes us good partners in this project. As said we are software engineers first which means we will focus on gameplay before nice graphics and other focuses. We strive for an experience which will bring you into the world of Brutus through the gameplay rather than the environment.
        </p>
        <section class="brutus-text-image-section">
